enttextdv: HSU students dress in a way that varies from fashionable youth counterculture to what I would call "Mountain casual" (patent pending).  We tend to be more casual, comfortable, and cozy, and there's a lot of hippie and lumberjack inspired looks.  HSU attracts both local NorCal students and students from central or SoCal who wanted to get as far from home as possible.  We usually aren't big fans of the type of south-beach party lifestyle distinctive of, say, UC Santa Barbara.  Many of us felt out of place in our hometowns, and I suspect many of us come from less-than-nurturing homes.  We care a little less about prestige than students attending, say, UC Berkeley or UC Santa Cruz.  Many students were attracted to the forestry, wildlife, fishery, and botany programs.  I think many of us feel lost.  Maybe that's why I see us as having a common sense of fate but not having much organization.
